flowRoot.flowPara: While preparing the slides for my presentation, XRandr worked but LibreOffice refused to use both monitor outputs. Thanks to E17 I could unset 'full screen window' and move it to the other desktop

Thank you for joining us at the openSUSE Conference 2013 in Thessaloniki. We would like to thank the local team for spending countless hours in preparing the event and all others that pitched in from all corners of the world. Over the next 3 days we will have more than 60 talks, workshops and BoF sessions to keep all Geekos busy, happy and interested. Have a lot of Fun!
* the entry hall has booths from our sponsors, partners and communities like Mozilla, Oracle, KDE and of course openSUSE!

* You can find room Zeus, on your left (behind booths). Hephaestus, the second largest room can be found on your right hand when you are past registration. You can find the smaller BoF and workshop rooms upstairs(check with stella).
* You can find drinks and snacks at the bar, just walk past the registration. The toilets are next to the bar.
* Outside you can find 'the beach bar' where you can get refreshing drinks and cool your feet in the small swimming pools.
* The beach bar uses 'Geeko money' which you can buy for 50ct each on the right side of the registration booth.
* Remember that for the workshops you should register in advance if you want to be sure about a spot. Find it here: tinyurl.com/qgqrc8t

* Next to registration you can find a table with flyers and information about Thessaloniki, public transport etcetera.* If you have any other questions or needs, ask at the Registration desk!* there is a charging room to the left of the registration desk. Here you can give your laptop, tablet or phone the juice they need to be of good service.* There is an android app with the conference schedule, find a link on the top-right of the conference website.* As you can see on the posters around, our hash tag is #osc13 and that's the group where you can find us on flickr, too.
* people take pictures everywhere, if you do, it would be cool if you could share them under a free license like Creative Commons!
* If you want to volunteer, ask at registration, we can always use more helping hands!
The Geeko on the window was made on Thursday afternoon out of 423 Post-It™ notes and it is the biggest Post-It™ Geeko we've ever made! ?
It came out larger than expected, and we needed the longest ladder available at the venue, and 4 people to make it, including a trusted board member for the official blessings.
The actual pasting of the stickers took only 11 minutes for that well trained geeko experts crew.
